JOB OVERVIEW
We are seeking an Admissions Officer to execute a diverse range of admissions tasks and support the engagement with diverse families in our community. The position will report to the Admissions Manager, be an integral part of the School’s Admissions & Enrollment Team, and work closely with many other departments of the School.

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES
• Manage the application process, ensuring a seamless and positive experience for prospective families;
• Advise new and visiting families on various aspects of the School, admissions guidelines, tuition fees and conduct campus tours;
• Represent the School with a professional and engaging presence—projecting warmth, confidence, and approachability when welcoming visitors, guiding tours, and supporting events;
• Support outreach efforts by attending external community events to build relationships and expand engagement with prospective and current families;
• Provide a high quality customer service to stakeholders, community members, prospective parents and visitors to the School;
• Oversee the organization of entrance exams, scheduling interviews, including liaison with appropriate Heads of Departments regarding the preparation and reporting of entrance assessments as needed;
• Support the planning and execution of admissions events to engage and inform prospective families;
• Oversee the logistics support to all admissions activities; ensure all School public areas related to admissions are organized, clean, professional and welcoming;
• Ensure confidentiality, accuracy, timely processing and digitization of all admissions related information and materials into the School System, including but not limited to documentation, assessments, notes, interest tracking and statistics;
• Systematically maintain and update applicant databases, information portals and hard copy files as needed;
• Monitor and provide the Admissions Manager with insights on families and market, assist in developing reports on enrollment trends;
• Collaborate with other School departments, such as Communications and Division Officer to carry out tasks related to school events and promotions, family relationship development and communication facilitation.

N.B.: These key responsibilities are not intended to be all-inclusive. The Admissions Officer may be required to perform other related duties assigned by their manager to meet the ongoing needs of the organization.

